<br>
<br>
ALL new applicants will need to have the following:<br>
<br>
1. A STABLE connection (Cable/DSL prefered)<br>
2. Playtime of 4 out of 7 days a week.<br>
3. The understanding that we are a RAIDING guild ...and if you are online (as a recruit OR member) you are REQUIRED to attend all called raids.<br>
4. 5/10 of the VT shards scattered throughout SoL        <br>
5. Emperor Key: at least 2 parts of the 4 are needed.            Preferably the ring and idol.<br>
6. The executioner's trial in PoJ must be completed for the flaggings of PoV and PoS zones.<br>
<br>
The following individual Class requirements will be applied:<br>
Needs for class: Low(L)   Moderate(M)   High(H)<br>
<br>
Bard: Level 63 (M)<br>
                    <br>
Beastlord: Level 65 (L)           <br>
<br>
Cleric: Level 63  (M)              <br>
<br>
Druid: Level 65 (M) will need to have MGB, Healing adept2, SCM, SCR<br>
<br>
Enchanter: Level 65 (M)  will need to have MGB, Gather Mana, SCM, SCR<br>
<br>
Magician: Level 65 (M) will need to have approximately 18aa (vague i know =p)<br>
<br>
Monk: Level 65 (H) will need to have Run3, ND3, **FD3 and Dragon Punch a bonus<br>
<br>
Necromancer: Level 65 (L) will need to have Call to Corpse<br>
<br>
Paladin: Level 65 (L) will need to have Slay3, CS, CA, ND3<br>
<br>
Ranger: Level 65 (L) will need to have EQ, AM3, ND3, CA3, CF3, PE1, LR2, Ferocity, <br>
<br>
Rogue: Level 65 (H) will need to have approximately 18aa (vague i know =p)<br>
<br>
Shadownight: Level 65 (L) will need to have ND3, PE, Soul Abrasion3<br>
<br>
Shaman: Level 65 (H) will need to have MGB, Cann5, SCR<br>
<br>
Warrior: Level 65 (L) will need to have ND3, Ae Taunt, CA3, CS3, PE1, LR5, LD5, PP5, PD3<br>
<br>
Wizard: Level 65 (L) will need to have SCM3, SCF3, **Subtlety a bonus<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Some may believe these requirement are a little too much..... and well...ummmm...sorry.  Also be aware that just because you may meet these factual requirements does not ensure you an invite...other steps will need to be taken as well ....ie:the actual acceptance to recruit and the recruitment period.<br>
<br>
Our family has grown to the size that we are quite happy with... but we also have no intention of turning away an exceptional player or character.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you have any questions...please feel free to contact me in game (at NON raiding times)....and i will be happy to answer them or be of any assistance that i may be of.<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
<br>
Ely~<br>
<br>
